Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into
½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites
from greens.

== Almond Couscous ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce};
cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring,
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings) and cover. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess
water from pot if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Carrots ==

While couscous cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously
all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Balsamic Cherry Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion
whites; cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Pour in @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit},
@cherry jam{1%unit}, and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings); whisk to combine. Bring
to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For an extra-rich experience, stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous, chicken, and carrots between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Garnish
with scallion greens and serve.